sections.title: Overview
sections.content_md:
# Overview

The `BuildDefaultFullDocPlan` function is integral to the core architecture's behavior. The `GenerateArchitectureFlow` method constructs a high-level architecture flow by analyzing semantically relevant symbols. Complementing this, `GenerateArchitectureSnapshot` produces a compact component graph, thereby avoiding verbose symbol-level outputs. The `buildOverviewSection` method also contributes to the core architecture's functionality.

```mermaid
graph TD
    entry["Entry/API"] -- 5 --> domain["Domain Logic"]
    entry["Entry/API"] -- 2 --> app["Orchestration"]
    app["Orchestration"] -- 4 --> domain["Domain Logic"]
    domain["Domain Logic"] -- 11 --> data["Storage/Index"]
    domain["Domain Logic"] -- 2 --> output["Output"]
    app["Orchestration"] -- 1 --> data["Storage/Index"]
```

## End-to-End Flow

```mermaid
graph LR
    domain["Domain Logic\\ngenerator, extractor"]
    data["Storage/Index\\nknowledge"]
    output["Output\\nknowledge, generator"]
    domain --> output
    domain --> data
    data --> output
```

# Key Features

## Documentation Generation

Documentation Generation: Generate and maintain the document model and markdown outputs. GenerateDocs builds docs from KG/index retrieval and writes model + markdown.

## Section Planning

Section Planning: Prioritize which documentation sections should be updated first. Implements behavior derived from graph-linked source evidence.

## Semantic Retrieval

Semantic Retrieval: Retrieve the most relevant code evidence for documentation sections. GenerateArchitectureFlow builds a high-level architecture flow from semantically relevant symbols.

## Source Ingestion

Source Ingestion: Collect and normalize source code units into analysis-ready artifacts. FromCodeUnit converts extractor output into graph-domain Symbol.

## Evidence Limitations

The current section is based on limited evidence from indexed chunks. Validate details against source references before relying on this as normative behavior.

sections.content_md:
# Development

The system's runtime setup and operational behavior are influenced by the `buildDevelopmentSection` method and the `configTableMarkdown` functionality. Additionally, the `NewGeminiSummarizer` function impacts these aspects.

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[buildDevelopmentSection] --> B(Runtime Setup/Operational Behavior)
    C[configTableMarkdown] --> B
    D[NewGeminiSummarizer] --> B
```

## Architecture Snapshot

```mermaid
graph LR
    generator["generator"]
    knowledge["knowledge"]
    config["config"]
    crawler["crawler"]
    main["main"]
    pipeline["pipeline"]
    main --> knowledge
    pipeline --> knowledge
```
